entries.name: PEMCertChainLib
entries.description: Library for managing PEM certificate chains.

entries.name: ForcedInclusionStore
entries.description: Contract that allows users to enqueue forced transactions via L1. The system guarantees that at least one pending forced transaction from the queue will be processed every 255 batches. Individual transactions may face longer delays if the queue is extensive.

entries.name: TaikoL1
entries.description: Main contract implementing the logic for proposing and proving Taiko blocks on L1.

entries.name: AutomataDcapV3Attestation
entries.description: Contract managing SGX attestation certificates.

entries.name: Taiko Token
entries.description: ERC20 contract implementing the TAIKO token. It defines a list of addresses designated as non-voting.

entries.name: SigVerifyLib
entries.description: Library for verifying signatures.

entries.name: RiscZeroGroth16Verifier
entries.description: Verifier contract for RISC Zero Groth16 proofs.

entries.description: Shared vault for Taiko chains for bridged ERC20 tokens.

entries.name: DAO
entries.description: The entry point to the DAO Aragon-based governance framework.

entries.name: MainnetSignalService
entries.description: The SignalService contract serves as cross-chain message passing system. It defines methods for sending and verifying signals with merkle proofs.

entries.name: SgxVerifier
entries.description: Verifier contract for SGX proven blocks.

entries.name: TaikoWrapper
entries.description: Entry point for proposing blocks. It enforces the inclusion of forced transactions after their deadline.

entries.name: VerifierGateway
entries.description: Gateway contract for the multi-proof system. It redirects proof to the appropriate verifier based on the proof type.

entries.name: SP1VerifierGateway
entries.description: Entry contract to verify batches using SP1.

entries.name: MainnetBridge
entries.description: Shared bridge for Taiko chains for bridged ETH.

entries.name: L1SharedAddressManager
entries.description: Maps contract names to contract addresses. Changes in this mapping effectively act as contract upgrades.

entries.name: TaikoDAOController
entries.description: Contract that maintains ownership of all contracts and assets, owned by the DAO. Its token weight does not count towards the DAO quorum.
